# Aura: AI-Native Programming Language

[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Apache%202.0-blue.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0)
[![Build Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/build-passing-brightgreen)](https://github.com/cybrid-systems/aura/actions)
[![Stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/cybrid-systems/aura?style=social)](https://github.com/cybrid-systems/aura)

**Aura** is an AI-native programming language enabling AI agents to query, mutate, and compile code via **persistent ASTs**, **static reflection**, and **incremental compilation** using C++26 modules.

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- GCC 15+ (C++26 modules; `-fmodules-ts` for older)
- CMake 3.28+

```bash
git clone https://github.com/cybrid-systems/aura.git
cd aura
mkdir build && cd build
cmake .. && cmake --build .
./aura  # Run MVP demo
```

**Output**:
```
Compiled IR:
IR: main
0.1-MVP
```

## ✨ Key Features (MVP)
- **AST Auto-Mutation**: AI-driven code transformations.
- **Static Reflection**: Compile-time introspection via C++26.
- **Incremental Compilation**: Change-aware recompilation.
- **Racket DSL Bridge**: Extensible frontend syntax.

## 🏗️ Architecture
```
Racket DSL → AST → Query Engine → Incremental Compiler
```

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Racket Frontend] --> B[AST with Reflection]
    B --> C[Query Engine]
    C --> D[Incremental Compiler]
    D --> E[LLVM IR]
```

## 📖 Example: Lucene-style AST Query

```cpp
import aura;  // C++26 modules

int main() {
    aura::AuraContext ctx;
    
    // Lucene-style AST queries
    auto functions = ctx.query("type:Function AND name:main");
    auto loops = ctx.query("type:ForLoop AND depth<3");
    auto high_complexity = ctx.query("cyclomatic_complexity>10");
    
    // Compile results
    for (auto& node : functions) {
        auto ir = ctx.compile(node);
        std::cout << ir << "\n";
    }
    
    return 0;
}
```

Compile:
```bash
g++ -std=c++26 -fmodules-ts -c aura.cppm ast.cppm query.cppm compiler.cppm
g++ -std=c++26 -fmodules-ts main.cpp *.o -o aura
```

